UNITED STATES of America v. Joseph P. MAUGERE, Appellant. No. 13547. United States Court of Appeals Third Circuit. Argued Sept. 18, 1961. Decided Sept. 25, 1961. Joseph P. Maugere pro se. David M. Satz, Jr., U. S. Atty., Trenton, N. J., Paul T. Smock, Asst. U. S. Atty., Newark, N. J., for appellee.

Before GOODRICH, McLAUGHLIN and HASTIE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This appeal presents to the Court no substantial question of law or fact.

The judgment of the district court will be affirmed.
